<br>
I was in a small guild in EQ KOV with my alt it was great bunch of people but one friend of mine in game was particularly a special person to me her name was Lyeanna. She was one of those people with a truly good heart and she had some sas to her for sure <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
After playing for over a year with these folks Lyeanna said she would be gone for lil bit she had some surgery scheduled in a couple days, nothing big she said. After two weeks of not seeing her we all got a tad worried. Our deepest fears had come true during Lyeannas surgery her heart failed and she didn't come back. I left EQ shortly after that, but I've never forgotten my friend Lyeanna. So the folks that say &quot;it's just a game&quot; I've got news for ya. Anytime you have interaction with another human being it becomes something more.<br>
<br>
So to Lyeanna I haven't forgotten you my friend.<br>
<br>
<br>
Deunset Thunderfists<br>
aka Cezzaar <br>
